orgAdmins.importTextFirst: Upload a CSV-file in the following format:
orgAdmins.importTextSecond: First name, Last name, E-mail address, Telephone, Language, Notifications e-mail, Notifications SMS.
orgAdmins.importTextThird: Once you have selected the CSV file to upload, click the Preview button. This will generate a preview of a portion of your CSV file. Data that can not be parsed or data that is invalid will not be imported.
orgAdmins.previewTextFirst: Before you can import the information, you'll need to "map" the information from your file to the corresponding content fields. The display only includes some of the rows from your CSV file because you only need to see enough to map the fields properly. The actual import will include all the data in the file.
orgAdmins.previewTextSecond: If you followed the CSV file examples, your column names will probably match the options in the dropdown. However, the options may not match if you are using a CSV file that you exported from another source. When mapping, choose the option from the dropdown that best matches the information in the column, or you may leave the dropdown selection as Do Not Import to leave that column's data out.
orgAdmins.previewTextThird: For each column, use the dropdown to select the correct content field for the information in that column. Scroll to the right until you have mapped all of the fields that you wish to import.
orgAdmins.previewField: You need to import all mandatory fields.
